attributes.background:
There is much media speculation about a possible state funeral for Margarest Thatcher and some indication that the present PM is minded to agree.  

This should not be allowed to take place:
Mrs T was the most divisive PM of the 20th Century;
She and her Goverment oversaw the destruction of organised labour and the UK's manufacturing sector;
In promoting a 'greed is good' culture she laid the foundations for the riven society we have today;
She failed her own sex - despite being the UK's first woman PN she set back the cause of equal rights.

For these reason and many more we believe she should not be accorded the honour of a state funeral.
